Example_1 = '''
Post:
 Authentic Taralli, a traditional Italian snack, offers a delightful combination of crunch and flavor. These ring-shaped crackers, often paired with wine, are perfect for any occasion. Crafted with simple ingredients like flour, white wine, and olive oil, Authentic Taralli are easy to make and can be stored for weeks. The Secret to Perfection The key to achieving the perfect Taralli lies in boiling them before baking. This unique process bestows upon them their distinctive texture and taste. Whether you seek a savory snack for personal enjoyment or a delectable treat to share with loved ones, Authentic Taralli stands as the ideal choice. Savor the Authentic Taste of Italy Embark on a culinary journey to Italy with every bite of Authentic Taralli. Experience the harmonious blend of crunch and flavor, crafted with traditional methods and simple ingredients. Whether you savor them alone or share their delight with friends and family, Authentic Taralli promises an unforgettable taste experience. A Versatile Snack for Every Occasion Authentic Taralli transcends the boundaries of ordinary snacks, seamlessly adapting to any occasion. Enjoy them as a standalone treat, pair them with your favorite beverage, or incorporate them into your culinary creations. Their versatility makes them a must-have addition to your pantry, ready to elevate any gathering or satisfy your snack cravings. Crunchy Delight, Effortless Preparation Indulge in the irresistible crunch of Authentic Taralli without the hassle of complex preparation. With their simple recipe and straightforward process, these ring-shaped crackers are a breeze to make. Experience the joy of crafting your own delicious snacks, savoring the authentic taste of Italy in the comfort of your own home. Prep Time Cook Time Additional Time Total Time Servings Yield 40 mins 55 mins 1 hr 2 hrs 35 mins 60 60 taralli Ingredients for Authentic Taralli 4 cups all-purpose flour ½ teaspoon fine sea salt, divided ¾ cup olive oil ¾ cup dry white wine How To Make Authentic Taralli Combine flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, oil, and wine in a stand mixer. Mix ingredients using the paddle attachment until a ball forms. Switch to the dough hook and knead dough for 10 minutes. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Bring a large pot of water to boil over high heat and add the remaining salt. Spread a large, clean cloth out on a counter or table. Pinch off a walnut-sized piece of dough once kneading has finished. Roll dough piece into a snake about 2 1/2 inches long. Form a tear drop shape, lightly pressing the two ends together to seal them into a ring. Repeat with remaining dough. Turn down the boiling water to a low boil. Drop taralli into the water a few at a time. Do not stir; they will sink at first, then begin to float. Remove floating taralli with a slotted spoon. Place them on the clean cloth and continue until all the taralli have boiled and are drained on the cloth. Place them on the prepared baking sheet Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Bake in the preheated oven until taralli are golden and firm on the outside, but still soft on the inside, about 40 minutes. Cool completely and rest for at least 1 hour before serving. Wrap with a clean cloth or place in a paper bag; store at room temperature for up to 1 week.
Title:
 Authentic Taralli Recipe: 60 crackers in 2 hrs 35 mins
'''
